data.description: UPDATED AND SPACIOUS 4-BEDROOM HOME WITH SCENIC VIEWS IN NORTHWEST ALBANY Nestled in Northwest Albany, this beautifully updated home offers a warm and inviting atmosphere. With 4 bedrooms, 3.5 baths, and a generous 3073 sqft floor plan, this residence sits on an expansive .80-acre lot, featuring captivating views of a picturesque wet weather pond. Upon entry, a welcoming foyer leads to an impressive formal living room and dining room, creating an ideal space for entertaining. The kitchen is a focal point, boasting laminate wood floors, granite countertops, a stylish tile backsplash, pantry, stainless steel appliances (including a double oven), newly refaced cabinets, a breakfast bar, and a breakfast nook with a bay window. The kitchen is bathed in natural light from large windows, including two skylights. The den area, adorned with laminate hardwood floors, a brick fireplace, and built-in bookcases, opens up to a screened-in porch--perfect for enjoying the serene surroundings. A spacious bedroom and bathroom on the main floor, along with a convenient half bathroom off the foyer, add to the home's functionality. The upper level features three bedrooms and two baths. The expansive master suite includes a walk-in closet and a fully renovated ensuite bathroom with new double vanities, lights, mirrors, tile floors, and a stunning tiled shower. The additional two bedrooms are generously sized, with new carpet, ample closet space, and a shared Jack-and-Jill bathroom, featuring a new tub with tile surround, double vanities, and tile floors. The laundry room, equipped with extra storage and cabinets, adds practicality to daily living. Outside, a screened-in porch provides a delightful space to relax while overlooking the pond and yard. The property also includes a double garage with an additional workshop and storage space. This home boasts numerous updates, including a 7-year-old roof, a new water heater, fresh interior paint, updated vinyl windows, and added insulation for energy efficiency (resulting in an average utility bill of $180/month). The all-brick exterior adds durability and classic charm. Situated in an excellent neighborhood, ideal for walking or biking, this property offers both space and charm--a perfect fit for your growing family. Conveniently located close to amenities, this home is a haven for comfortable living.
